        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I'm not sure if it's fully possible to have this fully typed, so either we don't allow `WARN`..., or we leave it as it is to avoid unnecessary churn and breakage.\n\nThat's a shame. Leaving it as is is what I'd prefer, but at least with more explicit documentation. Not having to use `vim.diagnostic.severity` is both more concise and doesn't require sourcing `vim.diagnostic` to construct the config data.",
