        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Currently severity is defined as:\n\n```lua\n--- @enum vim.diagnostic.Severity\nM.severity = {\n  ERROR = 1,\n  WARN = 2,\n  INFO = 3,\n  HINT = 4,\n}\n```\n\nOne option could be to change this to:\n\n```lua\n--- @enum vim.diagnostic.Severity\nM.severity = {\n  ERROR = 'ERROR',\n  WARN = 'WARN',\n  INFO = 'INFO',\n  HINT = 'HINT',\n}\n```\n\nThough not sure what other consequences this might have. E.g. it might be designed this way currently to align with LSP types.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-14T13:02:58Z",
